    "summary": "The world of neuroscience has swallowed me couple of years ago and I've been there ever since. I was exploring the different borders (or maybe rather dimensions) of this world, while being engaged into molecular, animal and human research. \n\nHowever, doing research is only one aspect of being a scientist. The skill of communicating your results and ideas to the public is often underappreciated. That is why I was always trying to improve my communication skills and release my creativity through the participation of science popularizing events, such as the Long Night of Science and FameLab. I'm also hosting a radio programme \"Pranie m\u00f3zgu\" (\"Brainwashing\") and writing on a blog \"Klub Jednoro\u017cc\u00f3w\" (\"Unicorn Club\")- these two platforms are used by me and my friend to fight against pseudoscience, debunk myths and promote real science. \n\nI was always enjoying being an active member of the community. Over many years I've been engaged in organizing events of different kinds, such as neurobiological competition for Polish high-school students, conferences and PhD events. Moreover, I appreciate philosophical discussions and a bitter sense of humor. I communicate problems instead of pretending than everything is fine. And I'm trying to be helpful when I can. \n\nI would enjoy to work in a cooperative and friendly environment, where people actually care about making the world a little bit better place. Or at least not making it worse.",
